fields.name: iTOW
fields.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch. See section iTOW timestamps in the integration manual for details.

bits.name: wtInitStatus
bits.description: Wheel tick factor initialization status (0: off, 1: initializing, 2: initialized).

bits.name: mntAlgStatus
bits.description: Automatic IMU-mount alignment status (0: off, 1: initializing, 2: initialized, 3: initialized).

bits.name: insInitStatus
bits.description: INS initialization status (0: off, 1: initializing, 2: initialized).

bits.name: imuInitStatus
bits.description: IMU initialization status (0: off, 1: initializing, 2: initialized).

fields.name: fusionMode
fields.description:
Fusion mode:
• 0: Initialization mode: receiver is initializing some unknown values required for doing sensor fusion
• 1: Fusion mode: GNSS and sensor data are used for navigation solution computation
• 2: Suspended fusion mode: sensor fusion is temporarily disabled due to e.g. invalid sensor data or detected ferry
• 3: Disabled fusion mode: sensor fusion is permanently disabled until receiver reset due e.g. to sensor error
See the Fusion filter modes section in the integration manual for more details.

bits.name: type
bits.description: Sensor data type. See section Sensor data types in the integration manual for details.

bits.name: used
bits.description: If set, sensor data is used for the current sensor fusion solution.

bits.name: ready
bits.description: If set, sensor is set up (configuration is available or not required) but not used for computing the current sensor fusion solution.

bits.name: calibStatus
bits.description:
• 00: Sensor is not calibrated
• 01: Sensor is calibrating
• 10/11: Sensor is calibrated
Good dead reckoning performance is only possible when all used sensors are calibrated. Depending on the quality of the GNSS signals and the sensor data, the sensors may take a longer time to get calibrated.

bits.name: timeStatus
bits.description:
• 00: No data
• 01: Reception of the first byte used to tag the measurement
• 10: Event input used to tag the measurement
• 11: Time tag provided with the data

bits.name: badMeas
bits.description: Bad measurements detected

bits.name: badTTag
bits.description: Bad measurement time-tags detected

bits.name: missingMeas
bits.description: Missing or time-misaligned measurements detected

bits.name: noisyMeas
bits.description: High measurement noise-level detected
